snippet: Teams like the Phillies and the Astros that have no shot at the playoffs traded away veterans for young players who could help them in coming seasons.
abstract: Tyler Kepner On Baseball column notes that teams with no shot at the playoffs, like Philadelphia Phillies and the Houston Astros, traded away veterans for young players who can help them in coming seasons.
lead_paragraph: Teams like the Phillies and the Astros that have no shot at the playoffs traded away veterans for young players who could help them in coming seasons.
